NOTES
-----

- Vim 7+ recommended.
- <Leader> is mapped to ,


SHORTCUTS
---------

<Leader>t     open fuzzy file finder dialogue (similar to TextMate's cmd-T functionality)
<Leader>n     open NERDTree file browser
<Leader>0-9   switch to buffer<n>


INSTALL
-------

When pulling project down with git, you will need to run the following two commands to pull the sub-modules down:

$ git submodule init
$ git submodule update

Then:

$ ./install.sh

If you have an existing .vimrc, it will be backed up to ~/.vim/.vimrc.mine
